data.content:
Here are the three EF Core 10 breaking changes affecting your code, and how to fix each:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — now takes a regular lambda, not an expression tree

Your manual `Expression.Lambda` / `Expression.Call` code **won't compile** because the new overload accepts `Func<…>` instead of `Expression<Func<…>>`.

**Fix** — replace the entire expression-tree construction with a simple lambda:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

---

### 2. Complex type column names — now auto-uniquified & nested paths are fully qualified

Two related changes:

- **Same-named properties** across complex types (e.g. `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street`) now get a disambiguating suffix instead of silently sharing a column.
- **Nested complex types** now use the full path: `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` → column `Payment_BillingAddress_City` (was `BillingAddress_City`).

**Fix** — if you need to preserve existing column names, pin them explicitly:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress,
        p => p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress,
        p => p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
});

// For nested complex types, pin the old name:
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>()
    .ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment)
    .ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress)
    .Property(a => a.City)
    .HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
```

Otherwise a new migration will rename your columns and break existing data access.

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method now requires an additional `string logCommandText` parameter (for redacted SQL logging).

**Fix** — add the parameter to each method signature:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)          // ← new parameter
    {
        // Use logCommandText (redacted) for logging
        // Use command.CommandText for actual execution
    }
}
```

Update **all** methods on the interface (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.) the same way.
